<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-23T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-23T10:00:00-05:00" n="180" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d180">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/384: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio
                                            de Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-23T12:00:00-03:00"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            23, 1918, 12 noon.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 3.57 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Statement of President handed to Da Gama the day Embassy received it.
                                Before receipt of message Minister had taken steps along line which
                                your December 4th, 7 p.m. suggested.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>